@startuml sq_obs01_stream_log
' ============================================================
' Title:     OBS-01 — STREAM Structured Log
' Boundary:  nasim code agent CLI
' Purpose:   Emit structured JSON log record to stdout
' Milestone: v1.0
' Version:   1.0.0
' Source:    docs/audit/audit.2026.06.20.logging.observability.car.md
' Review:    —
' ============================================================

actor "AgentOrchestrator" as agent
actor "Provider" as provider
actor "ToolRegistry" as tools

box "Observability Layer" #E3F2FD
  participant "StructuredLogger" as logger
  participant "LogRedactor" as redactor
  participant "TraceCorrelator" as trace
  participant "DualOutputAdapter" as adapter
end box

box "External" #F3E5F5
  participant "Stdout" as stdout
end box

note over agent, stdout
  Scope:
    - obs01 STREAM Structured Log — emit JSON record to stdout

  Preconditions:
    - StructuredLogger configured (level, format)
    - LogRedactor available for secret stripping

  Contexts:
    - Called on every significant agent event (turn, LLM call, tool exec, error)
    - Prerequisite for platform log collection (tenas pattern)

  Excludes:
    - Wire log append (WRL group, domain artifact)
    - Metrics recording (OBS-02)
    - Log shipping / collection (platform: log agent, Loki)

  Design:
    - StructuredLogger constructs LogRecord with trace context
    - LogRedactor strips secrets before emission
    - DualOutputAdapter writes JSON to stdout (always)
    - Human-readable output delegated to Renderer when isatty
    - Never conditional logic that changes semantics

  Returns:
    - Success: None (fire-and-forget emission)
    - Failure: stderr warning (never raises to caller)

  Invariants:
    - stdout only for logs
    - No secrets in emissions (redaction mandatory)
    - JSON format always (text is for human layer only)
end note

== obs01 STREAM Structured Log ==

agent -> logger : emit(msg, level, **extra)
activate logger

logger -> trace : current_span()
activate trace
trace --> logger : TraceContext(trace_id, span_id, parent_span_id)
deactivate trace

logger -> logger : build_record(msg, level, trace_ctx, extra)

logger -> redactor : redact(record)
activate redactor
redactor --> logger : sanitized_record
deactivate redactor

logger -> adapter : emit(sanitized_record)
activate adapter

adapter -> adapter : serialize_json(record)

alt is_tty()
    adapter -> stdout : write_json(record)
else not tty (server mode)
    adapter -> stdout : write_json(record)
end

adapter --> logger : None
deactivate adapter

deactivate logger

note over agent, stdout
  Flow:
    - AgentOrchestrator → StructuredLogger → TraceCorrelator + LogRedactor → DualOutputAdapter → Stdout

  State:
    - <back:#ECEFF1>IDLE</back> → BUILDING → REDACTING → EMITTING → DONE

  Failure:
    - Write failure → stderr warning, never raises

  Success:
    - JSON line written to stdout

  Key invariants:
    - Always JSON to stdout
    - Redaction always applied
    - Trace context always injected
    - Fire-and-forget (no return to caller)
end note

@enduml
